==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Skutterudite
<hw>Skut"ter*ud*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<ets>Skutterud</ets>, in Norway, whence it is obtained.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral of a bright metallic luster and
tin-white to pale lead-gray color. It consists of arsenic and
cobalt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

